Its a global gathering that brings together leaders, innovators, and stakeholders to explore the transformative potential of AI-powered virtual worlds in addressing global challenges and advancing the delivery of the Pact for the Future and the Global Digital Compact.

The event will feature high-level dialogues, interactive showcases, and UN-led project presentations that explore the role of AI-powered virtual worlds in shaping the future of cities and governments, transforming industries, **and strengthening governance frameworks** 👍

@everyone  Exciting Announcement!

The application form for general admissions into the next cohort of the Agents Development Class (formerly Discord Managers Program) officially drops tonight — Tuesday, May 13!

This is the beta launch of a hands-on, end-to-end program designed to take participants from zero coding background to building and deploying their own Gen AI agents inside Discord.

Co-developed by Dr. Sanchez, Oscar Sanchez, and our Network Architects, and facilitated by MIT affiliates, our technical team, and industry professionals—this is more than a course, it’s an entry point into a future-facing ecosystem.

⸻

How to Apply:
You’ll receive a Google Form tonight asking for:
    •    Your Name
    •    Your Weekly Availability
    •    Your Current AI Knowledge Level

Once submitted, your data is processed through an AI-driven cohort-matching system, co-designed by Oscar and me. This system leverages deep research techniques, learning science, and CNN-style parameter extraction to identify your cognitive patterns, availability, and technical comfort zone—then uses that to intelligently place you into a high-functioning peer group.

⸻

What Happens Next:

You won’t be placed into the Agent Dev class immediately. Instead, on Wednesday, May 21, you’ll gain access to the Gen AI Non-Coders Learning Group.

This is not a prep course—it’s a discovery layer in our pipeline. The goal is to observe your interaction style, gather learning behavior data, and give you access to interactive workshops, no-code tools, and prompt design sessions that enrich your profile for better cohort placement and give you additional learning in the meantime.

You’ll start learning, engaging, and building alongside others—while our AI refines the best cohort match for you.

⸻

Community-Wide Launch: Sunday, May 26
Application Form Drops: Tonight (May 13)

This is not just another class—it’s a research-powered entry into the future of collaborative AI.

Alright, I respect all suggestions, but deep down we all know **Madrid** isn’t just a choice — __it’s destiny__.

🇪🇸  Here’s why it’s the perfect place for our community meetup:
- **Top European Destination**: Voted “Europe’s Most Desirable City” by *Wanderlust* readers in 2024, surpassing Paris and Rome
- **Cultural Powerhouse**: Home to the “Golden Triangle of Art”—the Prado, Reina Sofía, and Thyssen-Bornemisza museums—Madrid offers world-class art experiences. 
- **Vibrant Nightlife**: From rooftop bars to flamenco tablaos, Madrid's nightlife is legendary, offering something for everyone.
- **Culinary Delights**: Madrid's culinary scene is a vibrant tapestry of global flavors, with over 13,600 restaurants from casual tapas to the finest experiences.
- **Green Spaces**: We triple the EU average of green space per resident.  
- **Excellent Connectivity**: Madrid's efficient metro and high-speed rail systems make getting around the city and beyond a breeze.
